---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Martial Arts — Combat Terms That Score Big"
  description="Martial arts words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. DOJO (12pts), KARATE (10pts), KENDO (10pts), JUDO (12pts). Fighting vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble martial arts words, karate scrabble points, judo scrabble, dojo scrabble word, kendo scrabble, martial arts terms scrabble, fighting words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Martial Arts — Combat Terms That Score Big","description":"Martial arts words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. DOJO (12pts), KARATE (10pts), KENDO (10pts), JUDO (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-martial-arts"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is DOJO a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! DOJO scores 12 points (D=2, O=1, J=8, O=1). It means a training hall for martial arts practice. The J tile alone contributes 8 of the 12 points, making it one of the most efficient 4-letter J words in Scrabble."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is KARATE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"KARATE scores 10 points (K=5, A=1, R=1, A=1, T=1, E=1). It's a 6-letter Japanese martial art meaning 'empty hand'. The K tile provides half the score, and the word uses very common letters otherwise."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is NINJA valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. NINJA scores 12 points (N=1, I=1, N=1, J=8, A=1) and refers to a covert agent in feudal Japan. Like DOJO, the J tile carries most of the scoring weight. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Martial Arts — Combat Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Japanese martial arts have contributed dozens of words to English — and many are valid Scrabble plays. These words specialise in J and K tiles, two of the trickiest high-value letters to place. DOJO, KARATE, and KENDO give you reliable scoring options when those tiles land on your rack.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DOJO</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JUDO</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KARATE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KENDO</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Martial Arts Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Best Per Tile</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">DOJO — 12 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">D=2, O=1, J=8, O=1 · 4 letters · 3.0 pts per tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A training hall for martial arts practice. DOJO packs 12 points into just 4 letters — that's 3 points per tile, better than many 7-letter words. The J tile does most of the work at 8 points, surrounded by three common letters that are always available.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥋 KARATE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · K=5, A=1, R=1, A=1, T=1, E=1 · Empty hand art</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚔️ KENDO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · K=5, E=1, N=1, D=2, O=1 · Way of the sword</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🤸 JUDO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · J=8, U=1, D=2, O=1 · Gentle way</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥊 KATA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · K=5, A=1, T=1, A=1 · Practice form</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Combat Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NINJA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SENSEI</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHOGUN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KUMITE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOKKEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Martial Arts Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">DOJO is a premium J-dump:</span> Only 4 letters needed, 12 points delivered. When you draw J with vowels, DOJO is your first thought. It fits on nearly any board and leaves you with 3 fresh tiles to draw.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KARATE hooks easily:</span> KARATE becomes KARATES (11pts) with a simple S. Play it near open lanes and extend on your next turn. The base word uses all common letters except K.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">K and J on same rack:</span> If you hold both K and J, play them in separate words. DOJO (J) + KATA (K) across two turns is 20 points total — better than forcing both into one awkward play.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Martial arts words are <span class="text-white font-medium">J and K tile specialists</span> with Japanese origins. They're short (4-6 letters), widely known, and score 10-12 points consistently. DOJO, JUDO, KATA, and KARATE should be in every competitive player's vocabulary.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-sports/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Sports</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best J Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/foreign-words-valid-in-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Words Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid martial arts word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
